column5: Anyone going to brave the snow on Lake Simcoe?
We were going to try Big Bay Point for Whities, havn't fished it before...Normally fisdhing Innisfil
Do u walk out or are u on a sled or quad?
Walk out, normally.  Tomorrow we are walking, due to low visability.  You?

sleddin........... have a few waypoints i wanna hit 7-12kms out there...............  bbp should be a better bet than  Innisfil. I heard the snow is not gonna be all that bad untill 3-4 pm.....  Let us know how u do and i will do the same good luck out there!
Dont forget your GPS or compass!  Good luck out there guys!

We're leaving Innisfil@6:30,heading for Island grove boat ramp,then along Lakeshore Dr. till Salvation Army then back on the lake for 12 km's to "The Spot"......We'll be Chevying it all the way...lol....TC and tight lines all.....Chuck.....

Will post results tomorrow night, ...........NO SKUNKS ALLOWED!!!  Be at BBP around 7:00am  Solar Lunar says 11:57 AM is the magic hour   good luck with the snow for those heading out far.  If you see us hitching a ride, stop and pick us up.
Everyone heading out have fun and please be careful.  easy to get turned around in the white-outs.  GPS advise or compass a must today.  Cheers  Craig
Anyone headin' out in this blizzard today fer a fish, is courtin' disaster.
I salute to the guys that are braving it right now.. ..
Current News reporting 0 visibility at Hwy 400 and Hwy 89. 600 collisions reported in the GTA.

Was supposed to go up to the hut today - but at 5 am this morning I chickened out! After checking on the weather stations and then the hiway webcams - I chose not to drive from Niagara to Innisfil towing a sled!  Good luck to any who venture out but please be carefull.    Don

Got home more than an hour ago ....As usual Shelley got her whities and a trout to boot....I got mine too, but took some time......Shelley had one up before I got my holes clean....Visibility was crappy ,but the GPS got us home without a hitch.....TC and tight lines all.........
Was slow out there compared to Yesterday Chuck.  Maybe see ya out there Sunday. You have a PM...
